\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Could you tell me your name and present address?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Margaret Sarah Axham. 123 Richmond Avenue, Islington, N.1.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 And you've never married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Could you give me your year of birth and birthplace?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 1896. March - fifty-four Penton Rise, Kings Cross Road, London.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 How many years did you live in the house where you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 I can only }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5572215\charrsid7944611 gauge}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611  it - but when the war came I was blitzed - and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 This was the 1914-'18 war was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 So you lived in that house until you were bombed out in the second world war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 You lived there for about forty-five years?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 How many brothers and sisters did you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Four brothers and three sisters.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Could you tell me roughly their birth order and spacing? Who was the eldest, was that a boy or a girl?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 My brother. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Who was next?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 
Well then another brother - sister, sorry, sister. Then another brother. And than a sister. And then another two brothers after me. Two - that makes seven. Am I right, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 You came next and then you had two brothers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Yes. That's right, yes. Am I right there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 And she had another girl after the last two boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No, before. Before me. It came before I was born, I was the one born after the girl I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 But she only lived a few weeks?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Could you tell me roughly how many years there were between each of the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Well if I got the big family Bible out it's all in there. I can get it out, it's - just there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Do you know how old your father was when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 I've got his birth certificate - I
've got his - no, I've got his wedding certificate. I think so, whether I can find that - I - I wonder where that is.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Do you know where he came from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Well, he - he said he was a - from Hertfordshire. Hertfordshire, that's what he said.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 What was his occupation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 A painter and decorator.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did he do this all his life or did he have other jobs do you know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 I think - he was - you know these beautiful plaster ceilings they used to have don't you, all the ornamental, well I believe h
e did that at one time. And then went on, yes. Just - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 He did this sort of work all his life did he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did he also do any casual or part time work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Do you remember your father ever being out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Oh my goodn
ess - yes. Mother had hard times when we was all little. Yes. Yes, we had an aunt - my mother's sister was single and she was in - she - was in service for Sir William Gilbert's mother-in-law, wife's mother and - she was there thirty years but she was ver
y good to - my mum and us, the children you know. She helped us - out like with lots of things you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Do you know how old your mother was when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Well look, let's say she died when she was fifty, 1914. Can you work that out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Where did she come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Wales.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did she work before she was married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 
Yes, that's where father was the painter and decorator there and they fell in love, she was the cook. Yes, and - Lord Bing. For Lord Bing, Carlton House Terrace.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 And she'd always worked in domestic service?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did she work after she was married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Any part time work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No, they never done that in those days, it was - not one of the things that - they did. If anybody - went out to work like
 that well - they used to feel that the husband, you know - wasn't - well it - it was never done, you know what I mean.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 You felt this would be a slur on the husband?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Yes, that's it, yes. Was never done.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Would be felt that he was incapable of providing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 
Well only when - the husband - was out of work, well like 'cos mother had seven children to look after but - I think it was - if they did go out to work it was only like - I was going to say scrubbing doorsteps in those days you know. No
thing like in service because they had the - the women in service in those days you see. My sister - my two sisters went to service.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 So in fact your mother didn't do anything after she married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 How many rooms were there in your house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 
Well mother had a house - rented - seventeen and six a week. Well - they all together until we were bombed they lived in a house fifty six years. But we had the bottom part, and mother let out the rooms. See, the top rooms and the first - the - like 
first floor and the next lot, top rooms, two rooms like on each floor. And they were let out at a very small - five shillings for two rooms you know in those days. To help with the rent, well it was only seventeen and six, but still }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3679910\charrsid7944611 we}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611  mean - well we look at it now as ridiculous don't we, when we - you know - it was a lot for those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 How many rooms did your family have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 We had - we had - the ground floor, not a basement, the ground floor and then there was a - a kitchen that came like onto th
e back of the house, just that kitchen. And then we had - before mother left, when mother had all the children, we had the first floor front, and the first floor - the top floor back.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 So while all the children were at home you had one room on the top floor?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Bedroom.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 And another one on the second floor?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 That's right, at the back.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 How many rooms were there on the ground floor? You had a kitchen at the back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Yes, well there'd - there'd be two you see, the same as up the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Two living rooms?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 
Yes. Mother used to let - the first floor back room to casual workers in those days when they used to bring - people out of - prison or - anything like that you see, to do with the church, mother used to let that room for half a crown a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did she ever do any cooking or anything like this for the people she had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No, they - they did their own, it was furnished but they did their own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 So they didn't eat with you or anything?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 How many lodgers would there normally be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 
Well when we all grew up and - older - there was two rooms at the top were let out. And then there was a - a first floor front room we lot to a gentleman.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 But when you were children these two rooms that were let out were they let out for one person?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No, no, different.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Two or three people at a time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Only two. One or two, we never had anymore, no. Or no children or anything like that in the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 You had four rooms for your family in fact, two living rooms and two bedrooms?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 How about bathroom and toilet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Nothing at all, toilet was out in a back yard. You had to go out - through the back and down the yard and there was the toilet.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did you have any relatives live with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Or lodgers actually share your accommodation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did your mother pay anyone to help in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No, she couldn't. Us kiddies done it. Mother done all the washing poor thing in a - in a - outside we had a - a wash hou
se you know, with a - big stone copper, and - us children used to light the old fire you know and get the water boiling, mother used to be out there nearly all day Monday washing for all of us. It seemed terrible when you think of it today you know. Out t
here and especially in the winter and all the washing used to be - hanging up in lines in our kitchen you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 She used to do all the washing at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Were your clothes new or secondhand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Well - mine was - mother did - make some
 of our clothes, you know, as - as best she could, how she knew, but - at Christmastime, we used to belong to the Baptist chapel, didn't belong but we went you know as children all of us, and - they used to have like a - a Christmas party like for a festi
val like to get money in and they used to provide - joints of meat and - at harvest time and - vegetables to go with it to all the families like that }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5572215\charrsid7944611 hadn\rquote t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611  - their fathers used to be out of work. Well then Christmastime, for us girls there always used to b
e little dresses. You know, I always had a dress from there every Christmas. And - Lady Gilbert, there was a - a - a Lady Winegall her name was in those days, I think he was in the Army, you know, but he was somebody big, and when I used to go to my aunt 
-
 when holidays came, which was - children - you know, school holidays, she used to have me always there because - I wasn't very strong and I used to get the best of food you see. And the lady used to know I was there, that was all right you know. And - an
d - we used - and this Lady used to see me there like, this - Miss Winegall used to come and she had a daughter and Mrs - you know Mrs Winegall, but the young one was - we used to call h}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5572215\charrsid7944611 
er young - Lady Win}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 egall you see, and - I used to have some of her beautiful clothes and my mother you know, oh I'll never forget it, had a most beautiful - Easter }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5572215\charrsid7944611 bonnet}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 
. Beautiful thing it was, white with pink ribbon on it and - mother made me a dress with all frills on it. And of course we were very poor you know and of co
urse going to Sunday school and mother did me up - dressed me up with this on one Easter time, and I went to Sunday school in the afternoon, it was on a - we had - Sunday school - you know, anniversary. And coming down the steps of the chapel - one of the
 
women there, you know, the teachers called, oh chase me girls, look. Oh - and I went home and I cried and, mum I'll never put that on again. Well it was ridiculous really, because - oh it was too - oh it was too grand. But it was really - when I think ove
r things, poor }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5572215\charrsid7944611 old}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 
 mum, you know, she done her best but - wouldn't go out in it anymore. I was all right - the dress was all right. And they were pieces that had been given - from my aunt to mother, they was like - strips of - red - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5572215\charrsid7944611 moir\'e9}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611  silk. And they wer
e all edged with black narrow velvet. And it was all pieces and mother was handy you see, and she'd make this up for me, all frilly frills you know, oh. And of course -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 When you stayed with your aunt in service in the school holidays did you used to help her in the house at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 
Oh no, I was only - I think I would been about - ten or eleven. Oh no. I used to be - oh it was lovely. Any - anyway I was there - I'll tell you when I was there, when - you remember the Sinn Feiners in - in - you know wh
en they - they had all that shooting and that? In Ireland. And we - auntie took me to the pictures there and in High Street Kensington to see the film. 'Cos - Churchill - was there at the time you know, during - that was many years ago wasn't it, yes, I w
as there then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Were your shoes secondhand?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 
Oh very - oh no. Mum wouldn't buy us shoes, we had to wear boots 'cos we wore the shoes out - wore our stockings out too quick so we had to have boots.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Were these new or secondhand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No, new. Mother bought new, well they were about - couple of - two and eleven or something like that in those days weren't they you know.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 I suppose with a big family as you outgrew them they could be handed on to the younger ones?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Yes. But I remember a t
ime when - mother - like we couldn't afford a pair of shoes - boots for me, and - oh I had terrible boots on and I went to school and I can remember it now. I sat in the classroom, and the teacher looked at me and she said to me, oh, she said, are they th
e
 only boots you've got? I said, yes, my mum can't afford any. So she said, oh I'll bring you up a pair of mine. Well of course she was much older than me. And when she brought them they was those button ups you know, and - right up and they were miles too
 big for me. And - yes. And - but I wore them, I had to wear them I mean until they could afford to get me any.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Would you father help with any jobs around the house, would he do any washing up or odd jobs like this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No. Never known him to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 How about getting coal for the fires or these sort of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Oh yes, he'd do that. Oh he used to like his fire. Used to like put - putting the - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 How about decorating?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Oh yes, he'd do that, yes. Oh yes, yes, yes. Oh yes, he was very good really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Would he help with the children, would he give the young ones a bath or dress them or anything like this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 He didn't have much to do with the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No, no not with that side, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Would he look after the children when your mother went out or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Oh I think so, yes, definitely, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did he ever take you out without your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Oh yes. Oh yes, and - if - 'cos he used to go to Vernon chapel, as he - you know, like when we were all young, 
and - he used to take me with him, and we used to sit at the back of the church. Because - it - - they had a grating there where the warmth come through. And - oh yes, he used to take me. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did he take the children anywhere else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Yes, we used
 to go to - every holiday time, Easter, Whitsun, any holiday time - me auntie used to come up from Kensington and we used to go up to Hampstead, you know, the fair. And of course coconut shies, oh smashing, we used to get plenty of coconuts, used to alway
s get coconuts you know. Oh yes, we'll always remember that. 'Course they was cheap you see on a - on - on the trams wasn't it then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did you have any tasks you had to carry out regularly at home to help your mother and father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Yes. My sister and 
I, we both had our jobs to do. Either - I used to perhaps do all the stairs down. And the passage. And my sister perhaps would have to do the kitchen and the toilet. And mother used to come behind me and she used to say - used to look over our work becaus
e
 she was well - bred you know in that kind of thing and she used to say, come here, want to speak to you, she said. Come up these stairs. When you wash don't you wash in the corners? And you know really she'd got something that she dug out, you know, 'cos
 in the corners of the staircase you do find when you're washing with, you know, like scrubbing and that, all the little bits get you know. And - oh she was through. Oh we used to have to go over it again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 How much work did you have to do in the house, quite a bit did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 
No, we were always allowed out to play in the street in those days you know, with our little mates up and drown the street. Oh no, we - we never had to do washing or nothing like that. It was only those kind of jobs you know, sh
e kind of trained us. She trained us, she wouldn't - let us be idle. She trained us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did your brothers have regular jobs to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Yes, my - eldest brother was - put to a trade, you know, learnt a trade, what do you call it - apprenticed. And he got on well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 But I mean jobs in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No, nothing in the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 The boys didn't help in the house at all?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did they used to run any errands, do the shopping or things like this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No, I think it was mostly the girls.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 How long did you continue to do these sort of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Oh, right 'til - oh quite - well see I was eighteen when mother died.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 You more or less did then until you left home did you, you helped out until you went into service?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Well - well I - I never went into service, my sister - my two sisters did you see. Oh yes, I used to do in the house - I did, yes. Oh yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did the older children help the younger with the things they found difficult, such as dressing or eating, did you used t
o feed your younger brothers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No, no, no. Mother done it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 How about the younger children, did they help the older ones or do any errands for the older ones?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 I - yes, I think so, I think that - my younger ones did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 What sort of things did they do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 
Well I suppose they'd - perhaps he'd say oh you - the biggest one'd say, going to clean my boots and I'll give you so much the end of the week, tuppence or something like that, you know it was a lot in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 This is when the older ones started work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 
Yes. Yes, that's right, yes. I had another brother that went into the Post Office and of course he retired - about twenty years ago. You know, they - they both - made way in the world really. My eldest brother was a - in the p
rint, I mean he - he got right to the top. Lithographic was it - what they call it - he used to assemble machines you know, big printing machines. Go out for - you know, all different places.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 During your schooldays were you expected to go to bed at a certain time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Oh yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Do you remember what your bedtimes were?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 
Oh - well we were let out to play but we had to come in at a certain time and - and have supper, we all had - always had supper then you see before we went to bed, it 
would always be - three slices of bread and dripping. Funny when you think of it. And if we were naughty - mother would say, well you go to bed without your supper tonight. And my sister, you know, she was a year - thirteen months older than me and she us
ed to say, oh don't worry. I'll creep and - I - I'll ask for an extra bit and bring it up to you. Funny.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did your mother or anyone else put you to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No. Oh mother used to come up and see that we - were in bed, you know. She always used to do that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did you share the bedroom or bed with anyone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 
Yes. My sister and I slept together. And in the first floor front we had two beds in there. And the three boys, two in the big bed and one in the other one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 So it was more or less girls in one room and boys in the other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 
Yes, but of course when my two sisters went to service I had a room of my own you see, and then the boys - they got married of course you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Where did your mother and father sleep?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Oh downstairs in the - 
ground floor back. And we had a sitting room. We didn't have a bed in the sitting room, that was - at one time we did but then they - you know, later on we didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 So your parents had one of the downstairs rooms as a bedroom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 That's right, and then - we had the other bedrooms upstairs, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 What room did you bath in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 In the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 How often did you bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Oh, we all had to bath every Friday - or Saturday. One after the other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 When did you have clean clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Oh every week. Oh yes. My mother was spotless clean.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 This would be }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5572215\charrsid7944611 bath night}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 ?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Oh yes. And - all - not only }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5572215\charrsid7944611 bath night}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 , medicines night, everybody had to have licorice - powder.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 You didn't like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 You don't hear of it today do you? Oh yes. Oh -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 It seemed to be quite a regular thing in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 
Yes, it was wasn't it. Yes, well I suppose us children you see, we used to eat anything you see, well I mean and you - and - 'course mother used to watch our habits you see, I mean -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 
You think it was more necessary in those days because of the eating habits or do you think it was just something they happened to believe in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No, I think it might have been something they happened to believe in myself you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Where did the family have their meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 In the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Were there occasions when you ate in another room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 
Only on - high days, you know, what I mean, birthday we used to go into the sitting room, the front room we used to call it you know and we had a big round - table you know the ideas.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 So you'd go in there on special occasions?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Oh yes. Yes. That's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Where did your mother cook?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 In the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 What sort of cooking equipment did she have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Well - mother always cooked by the fire you see, we had a fire - an open grate with the oven.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 One of these cast iron things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Yes. And a - a tap at the side where you boil - used to boil the water used to come from, but we never used it. It was never used. There w
as always a - a kettle on the fire and - in the winter there was always a - saucepan, mother used to send - me out for a couple of penn'rth of bones you now like from the big butchers and - of course the butchers knew us you see and - vegetables and we al
ways had soup in the winter.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 When was breakfast eaten?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Well anytime, I don't think we all sat round the table.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 You'd more or less get it as you got up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 What time did your father go off to work, what would he have for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Well I don't think we had a cooked meal. I don't know really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Would it be mainly bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Yes. Or jam I think and things like that you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 So the family would just have breakfast at whatever time they needed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 That's - yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 You didn't all sit down for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 What did you usually have to drink at breakfast time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Oh it was always tea. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Would you just have bread and jam with this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Just bread and jam or bread and butter. Or probably eggs you see then you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did you have anything different on certain days such as Sunday, would everyone be down for Sunday breakfast or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No, I don't think so, I think that - I think that we were all allowed to get up wh
at time we liked Sunday morning, I think mother used to keep us out of the way because of the cooking. You see?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 So Sunday morning people would more or less come down when they felt like it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Yes, we used to have to get up to go to - to the Sunday school Sunday morning. Me mother kept us to that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 While you were at school did you used to come home for your midday meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 What sort of thing would you have for midday meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Oh mother used to do quite nice meals for us you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 What sort of thing would you have at dinner time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Meat puddings and - oh we used to love - suet puddings, you know, we used to call 'em roly-poly puddings you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 The ones with jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Oh yes, or currants. Yes. Used to love that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 So you'd have your main cooked meal of the day at midday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Midday, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Would your father be home for this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Oh yes. Because he used to work just around the neighbourhood you know. He'd be in, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 What about the evening meal after school, what would you have then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 
Well just the ordinary - perhaps an egg or - I don't know, I don't think we had a terrible lot really as - as long as we had bread and butter and jam - and things like that. I mean we couldn't - father couldn't afford it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Would he have anything different for his tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 I don't remember really. Oh I think he must have had a - a meal of some sort, you know, more substantial meal. I think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 And then you'd have supper before you went to bed after this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 What did you have to drink with your supper?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Tea. Tea just the same, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did your mother bake her own bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No, she never baked her own bread.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Or make her own jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 They used to do that in Wales of course I me
an but - she didn't - never did it - I - well we hadn't got the - the fire wasn't good enough, not to bake bread you see, got to have a good fire.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did she bottle any vegetables or make jam or pickles or anything like this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Pickles, yes. She would make pickles.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 How about wine or beer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No. No, we never - we were a teetotal family, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 How about medicines, you say you say used to have licorice powder?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Licorice, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did your mother make any medicines at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did you grow any of your own fruit or vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 
Oh - one thing mother used to do - in the way of making things. My - some of us used to have a bad cough. And she would get an onion. And put it in a jar, cut it up - a Spanish onion I think it was,
 or was it an ordinary onion, I'm-not quite sure, and put the brown sugar in to get the juice out. And we all - anybody that had a cough, they - that was supposed to be a complete cure. But I think it did good you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 They didn't grow any fruit or vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No, we tried to grow strawberries once in our front garden, we had just a few, that's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did you have a very big garden?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No, only a small square. My brother had quite a few pigeons, and he used to take them up to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5572215\charrsid7944611 Hampstead}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611  and let them go, and they'd be home. He - he didn't go in for any pigeon racing or anything like that, it was just a hobby.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did you have any other pets at all? Did you ever keep rabbits for food or chickens for their eggs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 You never kept livestock for food at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 How many times a week did you eat meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 
Well I can't quite remember, but I think that mother - we used to have stews a lot. And - with the stock that mother used to put on like - as I told you what she used t
o get the bones because we had a nice bit of meat on the bones in those days sold, well then she used to - do as stews. And then another time there was a place up Lambs Conduit Street where they sold fowls and mother used to send us children up there for 
the giblets. So that we had the good - goodness out - out of that as well you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 So you think you probably had meat most days even if it was a little bit in a stew?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Yes, we had it most days, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did you eat tinned meat at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Never. Mother would never have any tinned stuff in the place.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did you ever get extra meat such as rabbit from poachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Do you remember seeing your mother have less food so that the family could have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No, I don't think she went wi
thout, but she saw that everybody - was well - and on a Saturday, my father used to go down the meat market. Harts - down Smithfield. And Mr Hart - 'cos he knew dad you see by - going there such a lot for the meat on a Saturday, and he used to say to dad,
 
if you like to come down eleven o'clock - of course the meat places were opening until past eleven, I'll see what I can find you. 'Cos he knew we - that he had a lot of children. And - he used to come - well I've never seen one since, a beautiful aitch bo
ne of beef. Aitch }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5572215\charrsid7944611 bone}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 
 of beef you know. And - oh used to have - gorgeous meals off 'em, you know, weekends and that. And that used to be sold, I think he used to get it for tuppence or threepence a pound them days. Marvellous meat, I mean you don't see it today you know.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 And sit in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Yes. Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Could you bring toys or a book to the table at mealtimes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No. Nothing like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 When could you leave the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 When we were all finished. Please mum can I get down?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did you have to wait until everybody finished or just as you finished as individuals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Well we used to have to wait 'til everybody finished.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did you used to say grace at meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Father did. Occasionally, it didn't - continue but - there was grace said, 'cos my father and my mother were - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5572215\charrsid7944611 Christian}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611  people you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Would this be on special days or occasions rather than everyday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 It wasn't - I don't think it was every day you know, just - different times I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did all the family sit at the table for a meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 When we were all there, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did you always have the same places?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 How was the meal served, did you mother serve it onto the plates form the stove?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Yes. All served individually.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Your mother did the serving?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Yes. Father used to cut the joint of course. It was always his job.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 What order were you served in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Well I wouldn't remember - I think just as you come along.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 You couldn't afford it if you did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Oh -
 what - steak at twelve bob a pound, my father used to love his bit of steak. Oh he used to love - bit of steak with a lovely bit of fat all the way round the edge - about inch wide. Oh you don't see that now do you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 So you'd do quite well for meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 
Oh we were all right in - the food line you see. And me aunt, as regards veg - fruit. What they had over - in Kensington, the hampers that used to come from Harrow W}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3679910\charrsid7944611 ea}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 ld where Sir William Gilbert lived, we used to have - a lot of fruit from there you 
see. I mean it was all - it was known, it wasn't - taken away like - it was known it was come to us you see. We were quite - yes, really, we were helped you see in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Were you allowed to talk during meals or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Oh yes, there was no strict -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Could you choose what you wanted to eat from what was cooked or did you have to have a bit of everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Oh no, we had to have everything, if we didn't want that - didn't like it you'd have to go without.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 What was your parents attitude if you left some of the food uneaten on your plate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 
Oh if it was greens, I never liked greens, they'd say, go on, you eat it up, it's good for your blood. But - they used to try and make us eat it. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 But they wouldn't actually compel you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No, not really. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 
If there was something on the table you wanted like the salt could you ask someone to pass it or did you have to wait until if was offered to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Oh no, no, there was nothing like that, you just took it if you wanted it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Could you ask for a second helping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Oh yes. If there was any left.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Were you expected to hold your knife and fork in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Ooh yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Where did the younger brothers and sisters sit before they could feed themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Don't think I can remember that - so far down as that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 
Do you remember whether someone would have them on their knee at the table or whether they would be fed at some other time or anything like that, or don't you remember any of the details?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 I don't remember quite - not - not as far back as that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 What sort of person was your mother, was she an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Oh she was lovely. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Was she very affectionate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 What sort of ways would she show this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 
I think she was reserved, but - if she said a thing she meant it. You know? I wouldn't say she was strict, but - you couldn't answer her back, you know. She wouldn't have rudeness.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 You always knew where you were with her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Oh yes. Oh if you - if you answered her back you - you'd get a good hiding. But my father, no, I mean - he was ever so easy going.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Was your father an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Was he affectionate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Yes, oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 If you had any worries could you share them with your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Oh yes, I think so, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Your father as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 So they were both easy to talk to and approach?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 How did your parents expect you to behave towards them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Well respect them. I - I think we did, I mean - all of us you know, respected our parents.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did your parents bring you up to behave towards your brothers and sisters in certain ways?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Oh yes. Well - as - when they got older and they went out to work I m
ean - say they wanted anything upstairs or anything like that you know, they said, well - you know, just run around and - do for them because you see them two boys - went out to work and of course they was bringing mum in some money you see so I suppose s
he - just - you know, let them - he kind of - helped 'em in a way you know so they wouldn't have to - yes, freed them, yes. Yes, that kind of thing, yes. Yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did they say you should hit back or not if another child hurt you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No, I don't think so. I don't think my mother would have - wanted that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 How about your father, would he have told you to stick up for yourself or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 He may have been a bit that way, yes. More so than mother, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 What kind of people do you think your parents hoped you would grow up to be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 
Well to - get on in life and - make a way for ourselves because - I mean when you come to think that my father was out of work - almost in the winter well - more than the summer because - he used to do ou
tside jobs you see as well, and of course there was a lot of - terrible lot of unemployment in those days. Weeks of it. Well of course - when - when they - as I say, mother put them to this trade but she need not have done. She - I mean, they could have g
o
ne out and earnt - I mean instead of going on a - a wage what you do when you're - you're being taught. That's like me you see, I mean, only had three and six a week. And they didn't get a lot, especially in the Post Office. And they - they sacrificed - t
hey sacrificed then to you see to get on - to get on in the world.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 To get them regular }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5572215\charrsid7944611 employment}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 
Yes. That's right. And of course the girls went to service because - there was nothing much - you see, they never learnt a trade, I was a bit - mor
e advanced you see, I - I loved my needle, I used to work - do little things when I was a kid, dressing dolls you know and different things like that. And even made a - a dress for myself, before I was - oh I was about fifteen. See, so I - had knowledge o
f that kind of thing more than - they did.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 So your parents were quite willing to sacrifice to get good regular employment for their children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Yes. Yes. Yes, yes. See they - well they didn't want - the boys to go to what father went to you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 What did they think of swearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Oh - out of the question. Oh yes. My mother wouldn't have nothing - oh, swearing, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did your father ever swear in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No. No, they were good living people. And they tried to bring us up like it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 When grown ups were talking were you allowed to join in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 If you did something that your parents disapproved of what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Well you'd be punished.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 What sort of punishment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Couldn't go out to play. That was one of the worst things really with children you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 So they'd confine you to the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 What other punishments were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Oh go to bed early.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Who punished you as a rule?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did your father ever punish you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Discipline was in the hands of mum?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did she ever give you corporal punishment of any sort?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Oh - what - oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 A smack or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No, a cane across me behind.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 So if you were really naughty you'd get caned?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did this happen very often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 
No, well no, not really. No. Well mother was one of those people that she wanted - you'd got to do what she - thought was best you see and - oh no, she really - bought us up - really, you know - oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 The cane would be the last resort would it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 
I remember - one day I was out on the street and I know - somebody said something about my mum. Or something was said, and I said, well my mum - oh - my mum's ever so strict. And - my
 mother heard me say it and she said, I'll give you going out telling people I'm strict. You see? But mother was that way, she wasn't - violent strict I don't mean that. But mother's word was - law, you know what I mean, if she said a thing she meant it.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 I suppose with so many children you've got to have a bit of order?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Yes. Yes. It's true.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Do you remember any particular occasion when you were punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Really punished? Oh yes. Yes. Children - well you know, as children we used to have
 games and that in the street, 'cos you're going back all that while aren't you really. And there used to be a little cul-de-sac turning where we lived. And we used to get up there with all our little - our youngsters we used to play with, and there was a
 
game called dead man arise. And it was that we supposed to - all get - about four of us get on the ground and all our coats - in the winter, all our coats came off, we was all covered up. Then there'd be - one used to be sent away, while that was done, an
d
 they used to come back, the others - some of 'em used to hide, and some of 'em used to be under the coats and I remember my mother - I was under there and - somebody was shout - used to say, dead man arise, you see, and the one that they got - called out
 
the name, if he was under there used to come out you see. And I remember I heard somebody - calling out dead man arise and I heard my mother's voice, she said, I'll give you dead man arise, she said. Come out, she said, you've taken your clothes off, they
'
re under - on the ground, she said. Come on, home - home you come. And I had a good hiding that night. Never did it again. That was the cane. Mother - of course mother said - with our clothes you see, it was hard to get and we was on the dirty ground you 
see under these coats. Oh the things we used to do. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Do you remember how you felt about being punished at the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Oh yes, didn't I cry. Oh I - I used to feel terrible if I was punished.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Terrible in what way, resentful?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No, not r
eally, I mean, I was hurt you know. You know, I mean - mother - well she only like - wasn't really hard caning but - oh no. I mean it really taught us that we shouldn't do these things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Would you say that you received the ideas you had about how to behave from both your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Both of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did one play a more important part than the other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 
No, they never inter - my father never interfered with my mother in - in how she brought us up, if she punished us, well - you deserved it. She never - he never - shielded, you know what I mean.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Do you think his ideas were influential in forming your ideas as well as your mother's.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Yes, I think so, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 When you had a birthday would this be different from any other day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Would you receive any presents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Yes, little things you know. Yes, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Who would these }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5572215\charrsid7944611 be from}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 ?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Well - from me brothers and me sisters.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 You'd buy your brothers and sisters a little thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Yes. Yes. I don't think there
 was much in that way really, we didn't have any - never had any parties or - like other children, they used to - used to have parties in the home, but - we didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 You'd have presents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 We had presents.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Would you have a cake?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Oh proba
bly my auntie, I mean - I was kind of - a bit of a favourite I think with her you know and - being always - going - I was the only one out of the family that ever went to stay at the - Kensington home. But - she always - she was always giving presents you
 know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did she give presents to all your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 
Yes. Yes. We were all treated alike. And also - when the summer came, my mother's home being in Wales, Bethesda, near Bangor - her mother - her mother was alive, they had a - she had 
a little - shop, you know, like a general shop, and - my - my aunt took every one of us - in turn each year down to my grandmother's. And - that was - oh the biggest treat out, we never knew any - none of us ever had holidays. Oh - well - the young - the 
boys, when they got a bit older, they went - when they started the - school - holiday homes you know, and you paid in so much a week, that was when they was - getting on like eleven and twelve, but of course - we never had anything like that at all.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Why was that then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 I suppose mother couldn't afford it you see. Well it came after we - you know, like later on you see when we was getting older.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 This would be your younger brothers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Younger, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Do you remember anything you did with 
your father or mother together on Christmas Day? Can you tell us anything about Christmas Days while you were at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Oh we used to go into the - front room, which was like - you know, and have all our presents out and - well we -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did you have a tree or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 
No, I never knew a tree. We never had any music of any kind, I mean - you know, we had no wireless - well of course wireless wasn't in those days. We never had any }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5572215\charrsid7944611 gramophone}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611  or anything like that. Nothing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did you have any musical instruments in the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 
We had a - a harp, a - a - I don't know what you'd call it, a small one like that, what - what my aunt brought back from Wales on one occasion, and - I used to try and play that you know as a kid but - no, we didn't have anything really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did you ever make music together as a family in any way, sing together or anything like this, did you have any musical evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did your parents play any games with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Oh we - we used to have draughts. And snakes and ladders, you know, that kind of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Your parents would join in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 That's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Were there any books in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Oh yes, we had books. There was plenty of - magazines we had like - well you - man used to come to th
e door, but they were on a religious nature but very nice stories in them you know for children and one thing and the other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 So most of your reading would have been this sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Would of that character, mother wouldn't let us have - books, you know, like ordinary love tale books or things like that. Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did you have any books from the library?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Yes. Had library books from Finsbury Public Library as I got older.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Was this while you were still at school or after?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No, at school. Was at }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5572215\charrsid7944611 Hamilton}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611  school you see, it was on our way - on my way home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did you have newspapers in the home?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Yes, I think there was newspapers. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Do you remember your father or mother reading at all, did they enjoy reading or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 
The only thing I can remember with father - oh yes, father loved his reading. Oh yes. I've got a book - in there with - very old book with all - I'll bring out and show you - show it to you, oh yes, and - I remember - he said, oh you should read the
 - I've never read the stories in this book, but - I'll bring it out and show you. But father, I tell you with father - it was always his job - of a - before we went to bed we used to have to get round the table, our kitchen, haven't got any gas or anythi
n
g like that, we used to have a - an oil table lamp, you know. Very nice one we had. And father used to - read a - passage of scripture to us every night. Well - he read it right out loud. I've got the old Bible in there, I'll show you that as well. And - 
we used to say, oh dad, can't you read a bit more. 'Cos we wanted to stay up a bit later. But }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3679910\charrsid7944611 we}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 
 always had to go to bed a certain time - read - all right then, I'll read just another couple of verses. I'll show you that book.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did your father ever read to your mother, or did he ever read any other stories to you apart from the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 
Well my father - was - a man that - he would talk out because - I can remember, you see he was very well up in politics. And he used to go down to - Clerkenwell Gre
en in those days - where they used to do the spouting. And Lansbury used to be - there. He often used to talk of Lansbury. And - and - all what I knew about father, about politics - from father, he used to always talk about things, so that's how we got ou
t knowledge actually you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 What were your father's views on politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Well he was a liberal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Do you know why he held those views?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Well at that time, I think the Liberal, then - were - a - a good set you know. And - the lots of thin
gs that we gained knowledge from him you see, I never used to read there because I wasn't interested that far. But not only that, I mean he would talk on anything. He was a very good -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did your mother take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No, I don't think so. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Do you know what her views were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Well I think she sided in with father really you know. Oh yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Do you remember your father or mother voting in a general election before 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Oh father always voted. Yes. My mother wouldn't because - women didn't have the votes did they then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Some of them got the vote just after the war didn't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 I can't - I don't think mother ever -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 And your father would vote Liberal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Yes. Lloyd George.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 In some places at that
 time men felt that they risked losing their jobs or their house if they voted differently from their employer, do you know if your father ever felt this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No. No. Well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Was your father an actual member of a political party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did he do any work for a party at election time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did your parents take part in any sort of political activity apart from voting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 He'd just go along to the meetings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Yes. Not mother. Mother never went, but father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Do you remember a funeral in the family, or do you remember attending a funeral before 1918? Your mother died in 1914 didn't she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Mother died 1914.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Could you tell us about the funeral, what the arrangements were and who attended and what you were dressed in, anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Oh yes, we all rent in - oh, deep black.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 You all had completely black clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Oh yes. Yes, that was a - that was the - in the day that - people did. I mean, most respect was - you'd got to go in deep black.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Even the young ones had deep black did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Yes. Yes. Everybody went in black.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Who attended the funeral?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Well - mother's brother was a minister. He was a Reverend Rees Jones, and - he came. And - another minister, Griffiths, friend 
of the family because they were all they were all Wesleyan you see. And he came. And - we all went to Vernon chapel. And Mr Moore, he came, so we had three ministers. And - and then all us children, my eldest brother and all of us. And - this was the part
 that - see we - we had carriages then. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5572215\charrsid7944611 Morse drawn}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 
, yes. And - we went - mother was buried at Highgate. And - what we didn't like about it, you see, mother was buried in Highgate cemetery because she loved to go to Waterloo Park, and my aunt used to come u
p and take her out you see. 'Cos she was in - not very good health, mother wasn't. And - but - so we had the burial there. But we weren't allowed - and I think it's awful - we weren't allowed a nice stone on the grave. She didn't have a private grave, it 
was just an ordinary grave. And all we were allowed was a - a tablet about that high. A wooden tablet on the - on the grave.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 I thought it was nowadays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No, it was then. And - we were - a bit upset about it you see because - we wanted her to have,
 you know, the stone, you know, so that it could always be there. But of course the lettering - was very nice lettering she had on it, but you see the rains came and - and washed the lettering out and we often used to have to go out and up there like and 
p
utting - put the lettering in black again. But coming back - but we didn't do this, but - coming back in the ordinary way of a funeral they would stop at a half way house and have a - a drink up, you know. But we didn't do that you see. Well we wouldn't i
n any case. But you see we had - we had two ministers you see, and they came back to the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 What did you have in the house, did you have any sort of food or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Oh yes, it was just a - a - oh no, it was like - like they usually have, a 
high tea, ham, you know, and - things like you know after generally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Were you taken out visiting neighbours, friends or relatives, you say you used to visit your aunt?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Used to come. Well we didn't have many relatives really, not in those days. 
We had - my mother - my father's sister lived in a turning along Kings Cross Road and she had - I think she had seven children, five or seven children. And as children we used to run round there and visit. But my uncle - was - he was a cab driver in those
 
days, then he - he got a car of his - you know - take of his own. But he was a very heavy drinker. And - mother didn't used to like us to go round. You see, because she didn't want us to get mixed up in - in their - that kind of thing, but me aunt - you s
ee, his wife was all right you know, she had a hard life too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Would this family ever come round at Christmas time or anything like this or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No, not really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 You'd just have your Christmas on your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Yes, we never had relatives. Only as I say, the aunt, the single aunt.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Were you taken out shopping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Oh yes, mother used to shop in - Chapel Market. And - I always used to love to go with her. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Your father used to take you to church sometimes, did you ever go anywhere else with just your father while you were a schoolgirl?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 I can't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 You were telling me you used to save sixpence a week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 That's right. Sometimes they would have a - a club you know and - we just put sixpence a week and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Was this at work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 With the girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 
Yes. A - a clothing club. You pick a number - oh you used to say, I'll have the last one, because I was a person, even then, I - I - I wouldn't have nothing that I hadn't paid for. I couldn't go and - s
ay get number three on the third week, get my money out to go and get a frock or whatever it was and wear it, not until I paid for it, that's how we were brought up you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 How did this clothing club work then, so many of you put sixpence a week?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 
Well - yes, well then they'd - say there was - thirty people. Twenty people. You - everybody paid their money in you see. It's same as like a money club you see. And then - so many numbers - to as many people put their money into it. And then - you go 
and pick out of a hat, well - say you picked up number six. Well when it - when you paid six weeks you had that money. And then you've still got to pay up 'til you come to the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5572215\charrsid7944611 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 nd.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 So if there were twenty people paying sixpence a week each for twenty weeks one person would take ten shillings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 That's right. Yes. Yes. That's right, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 How did you get on with the people you worked with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Oh all right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 It was quite a happy place was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Oh yes. Yes, quite a lot of - girls worked there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 How did your employer treat you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 
Oh quite good. Yes. Had a - a forelady you see and one big - was one - huge factory room with ever so many machines, rows and rows of machines.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 How did you feel about your employer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Oh, I was quite happy there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 How did you feel about the work itself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 I - quite interesting.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 You liked the work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Yes. Oh yes, we never - give it a thought, we knew we had to work hard. The harder you work - 'cos some were slower than others
, I don't think I was all that terribly quick anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did the job alter your attitude to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did you ever do any other sort of work before 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 What other work have you done since the first world war? How long did you stay in the dressmaking business?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Oh right up 'til when I left. I mean, when I retired. Right the way through.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 You worked there all your life until retiring?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Not the same place. Because the war finished - when we had the big slu
mp in the first world war we - had to get other jobs because it finished you see down there and we just - I just went round and I found a place in - in Duncan Terrace, Islington.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 But it's always been dressmaking, clothing industry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Still in the clothing, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Would you have preferred any other type of occupation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No, I don't think so, no, I was quite happy - with that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did you serve an apprenticeship or training period for this job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Well not really, I mean - they gave me three and six a week because I already knew - how to work. I - never had to be shown what to do.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did you belong to any trade union?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No. No unions. They used to try and - the men used to come round there at that time of day and - the bosses used to 
say to us, well if you see anybody outside to do with unions have nothing to do with it. No, no union.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Do you feel that the employers and workers had the same interests or different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No, I don't think there was any, you know, difference at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did you feel that there were divisions of interest among the workers at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 The - the - the girls - the women that worked there? No, I think we - we all - all was on one kind of -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Some people say that in those days there was a great division between trained craftsmen and other workers, did you feel any of this at all?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No, I never stopped to think about that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Would you say that full time work changed your general attitude to life in any way?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Well we didn't know any different did we, I mean nearly everybody had to work - a good many hours in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did you continue to live at home after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Up until 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did starting full time work change your relationship you're your parents at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 
Oh I think they - they - I mean, I think they treated us - practically the same, we might have had - as we gave up a bit more money you know, like money was - coming in - like, me two brothers were out - in their jobs and they were appr
enticed as well you see, they didn't get - bring in much money but - no, I don't think she made any distinction really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did starting work change your relationship with your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Well - not with - no, the older ones, 'course they
 went off and - and live their way you know and went out and - and about more you see when they started going to work so we weren't quite so much together if you know what I mean, as a family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did you spend your Sunday any differently after you started work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No, no, we always - always kept to the chapel. That was our main interest I think then you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did you take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Well listened - used to listen to father, he used to tell us all about - see, he was on the Libe
ral you see. Used to listen and - take it all in but - never really understanding it all you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 What were your political views at this time, before 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Don't know as I can remember all that far. Don't think I was very interested actually in it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did you vote in a general election before 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 
No, don't - don't think so. Did the women have the vote then? I mean - it was only like a certain age you could - vote wasn't it, even for women.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did you ever feel under any pressure fro
m anyone to vote for or support a particular party? You say your employers used to warn you against the unions?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Yes, yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did they make any suggestions about politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No. No. Nothing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did you ever take part in any political activity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 
How did you start to spend your spare time after you left school and started work? What sort of leisure activities did you have? You told me about some friends taking you to a music hall?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Oh over Canning Town, Plaistow, 
yes. 'Cos my mother would never allow us to go to anything like that and - this is when I was working at this place in Goswell Road. So - these two - Nellie and Eva, they lived at Plaistow and they said - you've never been to a music hall? I said, no, my 
m
other won't let me go. So she said, well I'll tell you what, she said, you come over and - we'll tell our young men that we can't meet 'em 'til later and we'll take you to this music hall. So they took me to this - music hall in Plaistow, and we went righ
t
 up - oh they call it the gods or something don't they, oh I thought it was terrible. Oh I thought it was terrible, all - all sitting on one like - weren't no seat, it was like sitting on - like steps you know. And - I remember it was - a piece was called
 
When Paris Slept and oh I think - thought it was awful you know, a lot of - smut you know, and - I - I wasn't used to that kind of thing. No wonder my mother never let me go to these places. And - I know we came out early and I said, oh I didn't like it. 
She said, you going to tell your mum? I said, oh no, I'm not going to tell my mum where I've been.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did you used to go to the cinema at this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 When the cinemas first opened at King}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3679910\charrsid7944611 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 s Cross I went there once. No - only - silent pictures you know. Yes, that's - never used to go, not very often. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 What sort of things did you used to do with your spare time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Well - mostly see as I say we were interested in the chapel. There was like - meetings in the week. And - there was only one meet
ing we never went to, that was on a Friday, that was supposed to be bath night. And I remember my mother saying, take your bed, you'd better stop over here, you know, but - I think that my mother was pleased that us girls went there like we do and interes
ted ourself in that kind of thing because she knew where we were.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 You started to tell me something about a cycling club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Oh yes. And from the chapel - they got up a cycling club, and - I think we had about four fellows in it and - about four or 
five girls. We used to meet on a Saturday - afternoon, - and we used to have club runs. It was all properly worked out, we had a little book you know, and who was - chosen the committee and all that and I remember one year I was the Captain. Captain. And 
-
 'course the boys used to help us, especially going up - we always used to go on the Great North Road, out Hertfordshire way. And of course you got some very stiff hills there. And - we used to go to a - a little country place, what we used to call our - 
h
eadquarters. And then - once a ; month we used to go right out to - a little place called - yes, I think - there was - a Scotchman, he came from - over Kensington way somewhere, and they had - the boys you see, mother used to like them as they went out to
 work to have nice suits and this - I don't know how she came by for this man to call. I suppose probably he came one day and asked you see. And mother used to pay so much a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 This was like a clothing club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Clothing, yes. That's the only one that I know of, what she used to belong to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 You told me that your father signed the pledge, was he in fact teetotal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Yes. But I didn't think he was - when mother first knew him. He wasn't a - a drinker but - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 And then he signed the pledge and gave it up completely?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Yes. His father was a terrible drunken man. So he told us, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 That sometimes puts people against it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Yes. That's - well probably, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 How did you get on with your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Well quite good, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Was there any one of them that you felt particularly close to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No, not really, I think we were all - together, you know. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 As a child who did you play with, was it brothers or sisters or neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Neighbours children you know. My brothers as well, my younger brothers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Where did you play, you said you used to play in the street?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did you ever go into other peoples homes to play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No, not very often. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did you ever go along to parks or anywhere like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 
Yes. We used to go - my - my brothers and my sister, we used to go to - not a park, but I don't know whether you know Exmouth Market. There was a Catholic church there, well there used to be - a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5572215\charrsid7944611 children\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611  playground there
, about the only one that - I mean, 'cos nowadays they've got them all over, and they used to - we used to call 'em the swing gardens, and we used to go there you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 But apart from that it would be mainly in the streets round about?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 In the streets, yes. Oh there was a garden in Pentonville Road by the church. We used to go in there and play.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 What sort of games did you play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Oh yes. Oh that was funny. Well skipping. And - we used to sit on the - oh our doorstep. We had a little path down. And we used to play - 
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5572215\charrsid7944611 four stones}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 , you know, like with a - what they called bobster and - you know. Yes. Oh is it }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5572215\charrsid7944611 five stones}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611  you know, yes. And - but this piece of - paving stone, at the bottom of the gate - bounced the thing up better than all the 
others you know, we always used to - I think in fact we wore it out in time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Were you free to play with anyone you pleased?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did your parents discourage you from playing with certain children at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No, I don't think they }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5572215\charrsid7944611 interfered}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 
 with what we did. I'll tell you another thing I used to love to do as a youngster, go and mind people's babies. If there was anybody that wanted a baby minded or took out in the pram that was me. And I never got married. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Was this better than playing with your dolls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 
With dolls, oh I had plenty of dolls. I've got one now that I had many years and - it was - a Lady Gilbert, Sir William Gilbert's wife - mother gave me - when I used to go to Kensington you see and - I've still got it wrapped
 up in there. Very old doll it is and all.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did you belong to any youth organisations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No. There wasn't many in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did you have any hobbies, did you keep any pets or collect anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Well I think my hobbies as a child was - 
making dolls clothes, you know, when I - first knew how to use the needle. I used to love - doing anything with my needle.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did you ever go out on a bicycle or fishing or for walks or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Well I was in a cycling club when I was about eighteen, nineteen. That's a bit too late isn't it, for your - oh do you. Oh. Now, yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did you take part in any sports while you were at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No, I don't think so. Can't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 You went along to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3679910\charrsid7944611 the}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611  music hall once, was that later on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Oh. Oh, that was later on, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 While you were still at school did you ever go to the cinema or theatres?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Oh no, my mother wouldn't allow it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Why was this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No, she - she rather - wanted to know - I mean, at that time of da
y I mean - they believed it wasn't - good for us children to go, not to those places.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Because it was sinful?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 I don't know, she was like that - when - we were growing up, I mean - she wouldn't allow us to go dancing. I think she - perhaps was - s
o intent in bringing us up you know, she was afraid perhaps we might say and - do what other people did you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 So she tried to keep you sheltered?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Sheltered a bit, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did your parents give you any pocket money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Oh - hadn't got it. We used to be thrilled if we took anybody - I took anybody's baby out and got a penny.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 You were more or less earning your own pocket money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Oh yes. Father used to always - buy sweets for us - and give it to us Sunday morning. Everybody.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3679910\charrsid7944611  No, he}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611  would. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Instead of giving you pocket money to spend?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Well they hadn't got it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did anyone outside the home help your mother look after the house or family, did any neighbours give her a hand at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 When your mother was ill or when she was confined to be having a baby how did you manage then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 I think father - did what was necessary, he was very helpful in the home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 He'd manage while your mother was in bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Yes. And I think us girls would you know, well we were brought up as youngsters to be - you know, to do anything, we - you know liked to.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did you have any relatives living nearby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 My - yes, my father's sister.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did you see much of her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Not a terrible lot. I mean I think she had t
o do - she was in the fur trade and I think her father - her husband - he wasn't a nice man at all, he was - you know, on the drink and if he worked he spent the money. So that - she had to do a bit of work you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Would she give a hand out if your mother was ill or having a baby or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No, I don't think mother ever asked her. Because of the husband you see, I mean he was a very - horrible man really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did your parents have any friends they'd }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5572215\charrsid7944611 being}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611  in the house or anything like this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No, I don't think we ever had anybody in. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did your father have any friends he'd go out to see or your mother?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Would neighbours ever call in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No, they wouldn't call in, but mother used to love to be out in the f
ront garden, and while she was attending to the - plants and that perhaps a neighbour would come by. Oh yes, she used to talk you know, used to - chat to them, oh yes, she was very friendly and - even today I went to see a friend - last Sunday, and - 'cou
rse I mean - this friend of mine, she's seventy-two, and she always used - she said to me, I can remember my mum and your mum talking on the doorstep, you know. She thought right back to that time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 It wasn't customary for neighbours just to drop in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Don't come in, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did your parents ever go out visiting anyone? Neighbours or friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 
Many people divide society into different social classes or groups before 1918, at that time did you think that some people belonged to one group and some to another? Were you conscious of these social divisions?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 
Well I was - conscious of people being better off than what we were. And - but of course being poor like we were I mean it couldn't be helped, because in those days - there wasn't t
he work, I mean, it was terrible - they talk about unemployment now but I mean - it was terrible in those days because - when my father was out of work there was nothing. You just had to depend - 'cos mother was a good - you know - very good manager. The 
way we - I mean we never went without. But we never got money - to help us pay the rent or anything like that I mean. Me aunt you see, she was very good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Could you tell me what the different classes were in those days do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Don't really know, I don't think I was - well I wouldn't have been educated enough to know that kind of thing would I.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 You didn't really think about it very much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 What did you used to think when you went to see your aunt in Kensington, you must have 
seen a difference in the way that people there lived?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 
Oh yes. Oh marvellous. I always wanted a - always felt I wanted to be in that kind of company you know. Well when I - you see - Mrs Turner, that would be Lady Gilbert's mother - my aunt used to ha
ve to take me upstairs into her room, and - I had to curtsey, and - and I - oh I used to think it was marvellous, you know. And I remember - she took me up there one morning and my aunt used to say to me, now be careful how you answer. And speak nicely. A
n
d - she had a piano in the room and I was very - as a child I used to love - oh if I could only put my fingers on a piano, you know, and I remember saying to this lady, can I play the piano? And she said, well yes dear, you can - just go over and touch th
e keys. And it was thunder and lightning. And I was sitting with my back to the lighting and - oh I was frightened and I said - she said, are you frightened? I said, oh yes, I said, the lightning}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5572215\charrsid7944611 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 s making my back }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5572215\charrsid7944611 h}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 
ot. I often laughed about that but you know, a little child you know it was funny. Yes. And I used to sing to her sometimes. But it must - be a hymn. She was - I think she was very good living woman. Very old you know, she was - about ninety then.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 So from your contact with the rich you more or less admired them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Yes. Oh yes, I thought it was marvellous.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Which class would you say you belonged to yourself at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Well how can I answer that now? I think we were just kind of - people amongst ourselves you know, family - as a family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 What sort of class would you put clergymen into?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Oh I - I - I esteemed 'em very high. Used to look up to them kind of people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Would you call them rich or upper class or middle class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Middle class - I should say, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 How about Lady Gilbert and people like that, what would you call them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Oh - well they were weren't they, elite weren't they really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 So you'd have the elite?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 And then the middle class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 How about your father's occupation, how about the building trade workers, what would you call them?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Well they were all very hard working - actually - they weren't - well some of 'em were middle class but I mean in - in - that kind }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5572215\charrsid7944611 of}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5572215\charrsid7944611 way}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611  I mean - they couldn't be anything else but - I mean, poor, if you know what I mean. I mean it was a very poor age that - I mean when you come - come to think of today - and how the money }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5572215\charrsid7944611 floats}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611  around and what they get, I mean you can't - you just can't fathom it out can you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Would you say there was a class below your own class at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Well - yes. Yes, I think -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 You had the house and lodgers, you didn't just have your dad's wages?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No. No. But I think - yes, there was a lower class. People that - were always in the pubs. 
'Cos the pubs were open all day and up 'til eleven o'clock at night. Oh yes, the - we - I always felt that there was a - a - a lower classes because we didn't indulge in the things that they indulged in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 You felt this as a child did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Yes, as a child, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 You'd look at some people and think, well we're better than you, or something like this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Where would you put schoolteachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Oh they were very nice. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 What sort of class would you put them in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 I should say they were a middle class. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 In the district where you lived who were considered the most important people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Well there were some that lived in the road that we lived in that were better off than we were. And - there were neighbours 
that - that lived there for years and years like we lived as children. And we used to look up to them you know. They were more - sociable I think. Not like they are today. I mean - I don't think the neighbours are - all that sociable today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 What sort 
of people belonged to the other classes you've mentioned, you mentioned the clergymen and teachers as being middle class, how about shopkeepers, where would you put them?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 I think they were hard working people. They'd got to earn their living hadn't they and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Would you think they were nearer the working class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 I should think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Or nearer middle class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No, not then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 They were the working class mainly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Yes, I think so then, yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 These are the corner shops?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Yes, and I mean they got - and they worked - they worked to get their businesses up didn't they, them little small shops. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Can you remember being taught to treat people of one sort differently from people of another sort?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 What sort of people would you say went to the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 
Well down Vernon chapel where we went - we had a - a big congregation down there, 'cos Mr Bryant, you know, he's there now - and - they were most of them living - round this neighbourhood. Whi
ch in those days - we said oh it was a - you know, we took 'em as being a higher class, you know what I mean? And they were always - well dressed, you know, and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did you think on the whole there was any difference in the congregation of church - of church of England and chapel congregations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Well - yes, I think that the chapel congregations were more easy going and - more simplified than the church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Do you mean less upper class type people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Yes, well - they - they do more - the partit
ion, church do in their service as regards they read off the same thing morning - well I suppose - morning and evening but - every time they - they read off the same - thing. But in chapel you don't get that. It - it's informal, you know, you don't get - 
t
hat kind of thing. They've got a certain way of - of doing their service but - they - they - they come out of like that kind of thing you see. No, I don't think - we didn't kind of run them down or anything like that but - it - it's what you're brought up
 in isn't it you see you know that - myself, I - I - I wouldn't - I don't care to go to a church service. I have been several times but - I'd rather - you know, go to an ordinary - yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Was there anyone you were taught to call sir or madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Oh yes. Very much so in those days. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 What sort of people would this be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Well - how can I put that? Don't know - quite know how to put that really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Were you taught to curtsey to anyone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Oh no. No, no, no. No, well we never met anybody really so - you know - important like, they were important people in - in our day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Who would you call sir for example? Was there anyone called madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Yes. I won a scholarship to go to - the Northampton Institute, and we had a - a lady }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5572215\charrsid7944611 superintendent}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611  there, we used to have to call her madam. And - and when I was at the Hugh Middleton school, we had to call our teacher sir.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Was there anyone else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No, I don't think so. Nobody else, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Do you remember anyone showing respect to your parents in this way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Oh yes, I think people admired them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Would they say sir or anything like this though, or would they address him as Mr Axham rather than call him sir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 I don't - I don't ever remember anybody calling my father sir, it would be Mr Axham. But never a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5572215\charrsid7944611 Christian}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 
 name, not like they do today, I - oh - I - do you know, I - I can't get in the use of - when people - I mean - they talk to me about people they haven't known very long and they get their }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5572215\charrsid7944611 
Christian}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611  names right away. Oh I say, no. They say to me, oh why don't you call me - Charlie or - no. I'm sorry, I - I - that's me you see, I think that - I think you lose respect for people.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 You prefer the more formal way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Oh I - yes, oh yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Where you lived did all the people in the working class have the same standard of living or would you say there were different groups?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Oh no, I think they was about the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Were some families thought of as rough and others as respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 I can't remember any really rough people. There were - a class of people that lived up the other end, and - he was a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5572215\charrsid7944611 boot maker}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 
. And - 'course they - as I say they were - what you call pubites you know. Not that - there's nothing wrong in that but they spent their time in the pu
bs of a night you see and all that, well of course we - didn't look down on them but - they weren't the same as what we were, you know, the idea you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 So if there was a division it would be mainly the people who wasted their money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Yes. But 
we didn't scorn them, I mean, I used to play with - their kids and that you know. I think they kind of respected us in a way you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Do you remember any division of this sort between craftsmen and labourers in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Craftsmen, I don't know that I knew any. Couldn't remember anybody in the way of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did your father and mother have the same attitude to people in different social classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Do you think your mother saw herself as belonging to a particular social class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 
Well actually - my mother's parents - they were middle class. I had - one of her brothers was a - minister. They were well up in that kind of thing, but you see, my mother - was a cook you see and - I think - in after years, when I went to li
ve - on - when I went on a holiday to my mother's - one of my mother's eldest brother's - in the Lake District, his - he married again a lady that - went to - to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3679910\charrsid7944611 America}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611  you see, they knew years and years before, and she revealed to me, oh in - I - I suppo
se I was in me twenties, I might have been in me thirties when I went there - that - they didn't have a lot to do with my mother - my mother and father after they got married because - they thought that she'd stepped out of her class and married - a man l
i
ke my father. He was a good man mind you but he was unfortunate, he - he wasn't - his parents were - poor. His father was a drunkard. And I mean they had a rough life of it. Just the two children. And I think that they thought that - according to what - y
ou know, and of course I was very disturbed when I heard that because it was my mum - and my dad they were - talking about you know. And thought that she could have done better for herself.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 So you think your mother probably thought of herself more as middle class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Well she probably was. Because mother was the poorest out of all of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Was it possible at that time to move from one class to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No. I don't - I think it was only money that got you there wasn't it. I mean, they coul
dn't could they? Well I mean - as - as regards mother I - I mean - she worked hard for all us seven children, I mean, in the home. I mean she couldn't - do any better could she, she depended on my father. As I say we had help with the chapel. And my aunt 
was very good, so we never went without.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Do you remember anyone being described as a real gentleman or a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 In those days, you mean apart from the - the family? Oh yes, I think we could - they were very kind. Some of the people we knew.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 What sort of people would you use the term about, what sort of person would you say was a real gent, why would you call him this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Well - taking it - I mean, there's - mind you I'm saying - there's - a difference in a person - that believes in the
 Bible and believes in God and - to a person that doesn't, but that still doesn't alter them, they can still be kind, real good people, without the religion, I mean that's their make-up isn't it, see - but - of course we came across a good many people in 
those days that - were real genuine, real - what we could look up to you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 So it would be more their character than their position?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 I think so, yes. I think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Do you remember seeing a policeman around where you lived as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 
Oh - many policemen on the roads. Yes. They used to walk along - from the Kings Cross - all behind one another, I don't know how many of them now, and all go on their beat, oh yes, I mean - there's plenty of police around.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 What did you think of them in those days when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Well don't think we were afraid of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 How do you think the police treated people in those days?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Well as regards - the pubs being open like they were we saw a terrible lot of drunkenness in the street
s. My mother used to send me out for an errand, and - there might be a - a drunk coming along you know or something and I - I was right in the middle. I used to be right up the front. When I got home my mother used to say to me, where you been? I said, oh
 mum, didn't half see a big row and a policeman. She said, I'll give you following the crowd like that you know. But it was excitement for us children because we - you know, we never -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 You used to see the police arresting people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Yes. Yes. Well we used to have pub at the bottom of the road you see. They could be a little bit - you know - bit harsh.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Bit harsher than they are now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No, I don't think they are really, they - they've got to be to some people, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3679910\charrsid7944611 I}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611  mean - I mean - give it out I m
ean you - you - you're - you're not going to be kind and good to a man like that that turns round on you and kicks you, and all that. You've got to use your loaf haven't you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Your home was rented wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did you see anything of your landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No. Lord - Mr Penton, his name was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 What did you think of him as a landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 
Oh very posh man. Oh he never come round to see anybody. No, we had a man - call for the rent, a Mr Croot. I've still got our - one of our rent books here, seventeen and six a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 When you were still a child were you conscious of your family having to struggle to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 How did you feel about this as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Well you just took it in - took it in our stride. I mean, it was no good us - you know - being any other how was it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 It made quite a difference when your father was out of work?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 How often would this be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Mostly in the winter. Because - I think he used to do a lot of outside work, painting outside you see. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 So more or less every winter }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5572215\charrsid7944611 you\rquote d}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611  have a struggle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Yes. As long as the rent was paid, the rent was always paid, that was one thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 The chapel used to help you quite a bit, and your aunt, did you ever have any help from the Guardians?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No. Oh no, my mother would never go there. No. No, my mother would never go. Not there, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 When there was someone in the district whom people disapproved of very strongly was there any special way in which they showed it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 What, my parents? The neighbourhood?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 
If someone they didn't like moved into the street or somebody particularly unpleasant in the neighbourhood, would the whole neighbourhood do anything about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No. No. Never heard anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Were you given any lessons by one of your parents or anyone else before you started school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Don't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 How old were you when you first went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Well in those days I think we used to go about three or four years old. I think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 When you first started going to school what time in the morning did you go and what were the hours of school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Oh I can't remember, I should think about nine o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did you go for a whole day straight away?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No, I come home - n
o, come - oh yes, straight - you come home like for dinner. And go back. At that time of day - you - you're telling me about school - we used to have soup tickets given to those children whose father was out of work. And we used to go Wednesday and Friday
 
to a soup kitchen that used to - a little hall that used to belong to Vernon chapel. And - we'd go in and have our - our soup. Well that would be probably a day my mum was doing the washing. Washing for seven - of us, in an outside - wash house, oh dear, 
when you think of it. My mother was washing nearly all day long.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Was this soup kitchen organised by a chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 What kind of school was it, was it a church school or a board school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 What the - it was a - School Board for London then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 How did you get to school and how long did it take you to get there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Oh just walk, Rising Hill Street it was in those days. Well it is now isn't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 It was quite close?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Oh yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Who went with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Well I think - us children used to all go along together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 What did you think of school, did you like it or dislike it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Oh no, I didn't dislike it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 How did you feel about the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Oh I think they were very kind. I've got a photograph when I 
was at school, Rising Hill Street school, sitting there like this. Yes, I'll see if I can find it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did the teachers emphasise certain things as important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Well I don't think I can remember that far back.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 How about tidiness and cleanliness and these sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 
Oh yes. Oh yes, yes, had to be tidy. That's why when - when - my father carried me to school one day, they hadn't got any boots. And I - you know, it was raining. And when the teacher saw my plight she - next day broug
ht up a - button up pair of boots - miles too big for me but I had to wear them. Until father could get - you know. I mean shoes in those days we could go - go to a shop and get two and - for a child - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5572215\charrsid7944611 children\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611  shoes you could go and pay two and elevenpe
nce for a pair. We were never allowed to wear boots really in the ordinary way - shoes in the ordinary way, it'd have to be boots. So as you'd get the wear out of 'em you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did you ever go to another school after this one or was this the only school you went to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 
I went to Rising Hill Street school to start with and then when I got eleven, or ten or eleven years old - I went in - into a scholarship, which I passed and I went to Hugh Middleton schools. And then - from there I went into another 
scholarship - trade scholarship, which I didn't pass, I had to go down to be medically examined on the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5572215\charrsid7944611 Embankment}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 
 offices, but - I wasn't strong enough or tall enough in those days, they don't take no notice now do they, that - they didn't - grant me the s
cholarship, but they gave me a chance of going in for another one which took me to the - Northampton Institute for a year. Domestic economy scholarship where I - I was further advanced in needlework, which I was very - you know, I loved to do, and cookery
.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 So you went to this first school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Rising Hill Street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Until you were eleven?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Do you remember much about that school, do you remember how you were punished if you did anything wrong at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No, I wasn't punished in that school. Oh wait a minute, yes I was. Had the cane.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 The girls used to have the cane as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 
Yes. Well I was out in the playground and - my sister, a year older than me, she - she give me a piggy-back in the playground and the teacher caught
 us. And I had a - a couple of handers for that. And me name put in the school - in - in the - in the book. Just because she give me a piggy-back, I ask you, today what they'd say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 They were a bit severe weren't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Oh they were, yes, you'd be surprised. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Were the boys and girls separate or mixed at that school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Separate. They were mixed at Hugh }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5572215\charrsid7944611 Middleton}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 .
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 You went to Hugh Middleton at eleven?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 I should think so, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 How long were you there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 I think I 
left - I must have left before I was thirteen. 'Cos I had a - a - a twelve month there and they wanted me up - they put me in for another examination, thought I'd - could do a further - another twelve months at the Holloway Institute. But - mother said no
, she said - let her go to work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 What sort of school was the Hugh Middleton school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 
Well it's a second - a secondary school isn't it there. Not like it is - we didn't have no 'O' levels and all that business, it was just a - a - a bit higher teac
hing. And more subjects you see than the other one. Mind you, Hugh - Rising Hill Street school was a very poor school because it was in a very poor neighbourhood you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 How did you like Hugh Middleton school, did you enjoy it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Oh yes, yes, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 How about the teachers there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Men teachers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did they emphasise anything in particular as being important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Yes, I was a chatterbox. He called me out one Friday afternoon - and - he said - I suppose I chatted in between the lessons
 you see and - he was going to give a - a - a postcard to the best - best one in the class. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5572215\charrsid7944611 
Well I was called out and they gave me a postcard and on it, it had got a magpie, bird - the bird of a magpie noted for it's chatting. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 I ought to have kept that and framed it didn't I?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 If you did anything that the teachers disapproved of at Hugh Middleton school what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Oh you'd have to go outside and into the hall. And wait there until the head - headmistress saw you and then she would ask you 
what you were out there for. Oh I think they was - very disciplined in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did they give the girls the cane there as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 There? No, I don't think they did, not there. You see, it was a disgrace for - the headmistress to see you. But I 
never got into very much trouble really, you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Was that a mixed school too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Hugh Middleton was mixed. YES.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Was this mixed in the class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 In the class, yes. I had a boy sitting next to me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did they get the cane or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 N
o, I don't think they got they cane, I think we had to write out - so many hundred times. I must not talk, I must not talk. After school hours, you had to kept in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did your parents show an interest in your schoolwork?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did they used to ask you what you did at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Yes, well you used to get a - little note come home you see with all how you got on in different things you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did your parents ever visit the school at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Only on one occasion, at Rising Hill S
treet school when my brother - was - got into trouble. I don't know what he did, it wasn't a lot because I don't think we were bad children that far, you know, wasn't trouble some. And - there was a - a - a woman teacher, and she punched him or hit him ha
r
d across the ears. And when the boy came home he had the earache, and my mother - the first I ever knew my mother to go up to defend her children because - my mother believed that if you did wrong you should be punished. Only in the right way. And - of co
u
rse mother gave it to her you see, I mean she told her what she thought of her and - and without swearing, nothing like that, mother wasn't that sort. But - the woman - apologized. 'Cos I mean it was awful to hit a boy across the ears you know. She just g
ive him one - one bash like that. That's the only time I ever remember my - my mother going up to defend her child.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did they ever meet the teachers apart from this or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No, there was no - not like - not like they do - in recent years. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did the other children come from similar types of home to your own or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did the teachers single out some children for different treatment from the others?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Were there any gangs or groups in the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No, not in those days. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Or any children left out of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No, I don't think so, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 From Hugh Middleton?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 I must have left Hugh Middleton about - see I went in for another scholarship, I suppose I - I - I'd been - about a couple of y
ears I suppose I'd been at - Hugh Middleton. It - well it'd bring me up to thirteen because I mean in those days you'd leave school at fourteen anyway. So - I should think it was about - between twelve and thirteen I was - I went through the scholarship.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Where did you go from there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Northampton Institute.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 What was that for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Domestic economy. That's - like - dressmaking, cookery, housewifery, all things like that. Yes, fifteen at the North - at the - }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5572215\charrsid7944611 Northern}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611  - Polytechnic, but mother said, no. She said -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 So you were at the Northampton Institute from round about the age of thirteen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Yes, to about a year, yes. A year, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 And you had the chance of going on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Yes, but I didn't go, but there - I - when I was leaving there - the lady }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5572215\charrsid7944611 
superintendent}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 
, Miss Tuck, she thought - she wanted to see my mother, and they thought I was too frail - really, 'cos I was, you know, very thin as a child, and - to go out to work. Could I - could mother keep me home, 'cos father then was -
 getting on better in - you know, in his works and that you see and - could mother keep me at home for a while. So mother did. But there came a time that mother thought I - ought to start going out you see. And - so she - I don't know whether she went to 
s
ee Miss Tuck. But anyway - oh no, I think Miss Tuck wrote her a letter and asked if I was still at home, and if I would go up there she would - get me a job. Which she did, and she sent me down - was a factory in Goswell Road, dressmaking factory - and I 
went down there as a learner. Well I knew a bit of the work so I got - three and six instead of half a crown for learning. Three and six for learning.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 How long were you at home before you started work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 I should say about four or five months.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 It wasn't very long?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No, it wasn't very long.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Would you have stayed longer if you'd had the opportunity at school, would you have liked to have gone on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Yes, I think I would have done. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did you attend any part time education after this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 
Only at the - Northampton Institute. We could go and do any evening work there such as drawing or - anything lie that, but - it didn't last, I mean I went and then I - wasn't very - interested you know. It soon dropped off, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Do you have any regrets about your education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No, none at all. I must have been a little advanced to have like - got so far as Hugh Middleton school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Do you think you benefited from attending school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Oh yes. Yes. Didn't have much - time out, I mean, I - we - always wanted to be there. Only when that was illness you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 While you were still at school did you have any part time job or any means of earning a little regular money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 What hours did you work in the job in the dressmaking factory?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Eight o'clock 'til half past six.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 How about Saturdays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Yes, Saturday morning. 'Til twelve o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 What exactly did you have to do in this job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 We had bundles of work already cut. It could be a bundle of - of schoo
l dresses, navy blue. It could have been a bundle of what we call roofer coats, thick - material. And - for one coat, child's coat - you would - have to bind all the seams, 'cos it was too thick to go under the machine. And for that coat - you would get p
e
rhaps elevenpence. For one coat. So what we used to do - we used to get - do all collars all in a string and all the binding all in a string and then when that was all done - then we used to - assemble them together on a machine. Well for a child's dress 
-
 with long sleeves, and all the seams neatened we used to get sevenpence. So you can guess what we earnt - earnt at the end of the week. And that was piece work. That was after we'd had our half a crown or whatever - three and six a week to learn the trad
e.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 How long did they pay you this three and six before you went on piecework?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Oh about six months.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 How much could you earn once you'd got on piecework?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Oh - the first - the first time I earned ten bob. Oh I had a little then - ten shi
lling piece, I wasn't half pleased when I brought it home to my mum. She give me sixpence out of it. 'Course that was a lot in them - in them days you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 You used to give your wages to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Yes. All of it, yes, and she used to give us
 some back. And then I gradually got on better, but I think the most I ever earnt then was about thirty bob, twenty-seven bob. And I - of course the most any of 'em earnt - I mean it was a big wage then if - if one girl earned two pound, I mean, it was en
ormous wage in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did you feel it was a fair wage or not at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Oh no, sweated labour. Couldn't do nothing about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did you have any holidays with pay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Oh no. No, they never had any holidays. Never had a holiday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 How much of your wages did your mother give you back on average?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 When I first - oh about - I think - I used to have about - three and six a week after a time. Well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 What did you used to spend this on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Oh always put something away for your clothes. Oh, sixpence a week.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Do you remember any other outings with your parents, Bank Holiday for example?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Yes. Father used to take us up to Hampstead Heath. Because - bit of excitement for the - for us children with the fairground you know.
 And - he always used to get a coconut for us and we thought it was marvellous.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did you have any pocket money to spend on these days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Oh - well it wouldn't be much anyway, probably we did. I suppose threepence would be - quite a - a big amount for us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did you ever go to Southend or the seaside?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 
Yes. Over the Vernon chapel - the Sunday school used to have outings. We used to go to Dovercourt, Herne Bay, Clacton. Just one day in the year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did you ever go away for a holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Only when my aunt used to take me to Kensington to where she was in service. But I never went - anywhere else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 As a family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 You said your aunt took one of you to Wales each year?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Each year, yes. To Bethesda, my mother's birthplace.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Who did you used to stay with there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 
My grandmother. She had - a general shop. Just a small general shop with - where there was a few cottages you know, and - oh it was - used to be lovely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 How long did you stay in Bethesda?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Well I should imagine it was about two weeks.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 And your aunt would take one child each year?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Each year, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 What sort of things did you get up to in Bethesda on holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 I could tell you one thing. 'Course I got out to - play with the 
- next door neighbours what - children. And - my grandmother - to get to our house - used to have to go down some steps. And - the houses were on level, the roofs were on level with the road up}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3679910\charrsid7944611  above.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611  And - and - this - little friend that I was with said t
o me, I bet you wouldn't go up that drainpipe and on - onto the roof and out onto the road. And I was only daring and I said - oh yes, I will. She said I can do it. So I saw her go first and she came back and down. And then she said, now go on, you said y
o
u could do it. So up I went. I didn't get very far, somebody had seen me, went in to tell my grandmother. She come running out. And she called me. And I looked down and her face and her first, and - and I did get a good hiding for going up the drainpipe. 
Would you believe it? I could have only been about - I don't know, about - I think auntie used to take us when we was about nine or ten. I can remember it as - you know, I've got a very good memory for years ago.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did you go more than one year?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No, only once. Only once, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 So you only met your granny the once?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Yes, just the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5572215\charrsid7944611 once}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 . And I had - an aunt there, living round - this - road, right the way round and over the other side. I used to go there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 You used to have Sunday school outings to the seaside, could you tell me about Sundays in those days, how you spent your Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Yes, Sunday morning - we - us children used to have to go to the chapel for the - Sunday morning service.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 What denomination was this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Baptist.
 Vernon chapel. Sunday afternoon was Sunday school. And Sunday evening it was - in the schoolroom they used to have - in those days you get crowds and crowds of children, a lovely Sunday school. Sunday evening meeting for the children. Well they used to g
ive us then lantern slides. And it nearly always used to be on temperance. And - pictures used to be where - the man came home drunk and the children, you know, all had to run out of the house and - it was a real - like a real story and we were really }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5572215\charrsid7944611 engrossed}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611  in that kind of thing you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 So they'd try and make something more entertaining of the evening meeting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Yes, in the evening, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Were there any other social activities organised by the chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Yes, as I got older - we went to a Christian Endeavour meeting on a Tuesday.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Would this be while you were still at school or afterwards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 
No, while we were still at school. We seemed to be - mostly - well my sister and I were mostly at the chapel. I - I suppose that was our - life then you know, with our parents.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did your parents attend a place of worship?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 
Father always used to. He always - always used to take me upstairs, 'cos I - I used to - be a bit of a pickle I think in those days. Not naughty really, but - you 
know, a bit lively I suppose as a child. And we used to sit at the back of the chapel where there was like a radiator underneath. Father always used to love to sit there because it was lovely and warm in the winter.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Your father would go every Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Every Sunday evening.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Would your mother go at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No - the - some of the ladies from the church - would come and visit her in the week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did your parents think it wrong to work or play on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 You weren't allowed to play games?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 
No. No. Nor - nor - have a needle in your hand or - clean your shoes, all things like that. All that had to be done on a Saturday ready for Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Would you be allowed to go for a walk in the park or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Oh yes. Oh yes. Yes. So long as we'd been to Sunday school we could go - out - anywhere we liked you know then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 But you wouldn't be allowed to actually play games?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No, actually what - my brother and I used to do. We used to go down in the City and go and se
e all the old buildings. You know? Probably used to do that on a Sunday. Just -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 See the sights like St }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5572215\charrsid7944611 Paul\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611  or the Tower?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Well not quite as far as that but down into - say round the - museum, you know, the - whatsname museum, what do they call it?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 The South Kensington one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 
No, no, this one here. In - near Holborn. No, there is a museum there. Whatever did they call it? No I can't think. It's a very - a very old - I mean, it's a big place. We used to do things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did you have a different set of clothes for Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Oh yes, always. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 How about Saturdays, how would you spend your Saturday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Well Saturday used to be cleaning day. 'Cos we all had little jobs to do. One would do the passage and the stairs. An
d - then - my other sister - another one of us used to do outside toilet and - the kitchen. Or the boys bedroom upstairs. We used to have - have to do - us girls used to have to do the jobs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 How about your brothers, did they have jobs to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Oh no, they didn't do anything. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 What would you do after you'd finished all your chores?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Oh well then you could go out to work - out to play.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did you do anything special on Saturdays or just the usual childish games?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No, just ordinary.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did you belong to the choir at the chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Yes. Junior choir.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did they have any special treats, everyone would go on the Sunday school outing, but did the choir have a special occasion?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Yes, we used to - we used to - have a - rehear
sals once a week, because - we belonged to the - choral - London - North London Choral Society which was in those days, and - but we used to go to the Crystal Palace once a year, we all had to know our parts properly - to go, they were very - sure that we
 knew and how many }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5572215\charrsid7944611 attendances}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 
 we made. And then we used to go as a choir and Sir Henry Wood used to take it. And it was really a marvellous - affair for us, you know, us children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Could you describe it a little?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Yes, they used to - yes, the cho
ir - 'course used to be like - tiers and tiers and tiers and we all used to have different coloured papers. Kind of an oblong shaped paper and we used to have to watch Sir Henry Wood, what he did, and then we used to move these papers about, so that to th
e crowds that were watching it must have been a very pretty - sight. Different way, yes, like this way - perhaps he'd say, one side go that way and the other side would go that way, and make all kinds of - patterns.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 This was while you were still singing was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 
No, while we - well we stood up and had to do it. And then we had so many - songs to sing. And of course we used to - go off for about an hour or so and have a - all the way round the Palace used to have these side shows and - games and tha
t. And then we used to have to come back again. 'Cos that was a break for a cup of tea I expect. Then go back again and finish the - afternoon.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did the chapel run a temperance club, they say they gave you temperance lectures, did you sign the pledge or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Oh yes, I signed the pledge, yes. Broken it many times since - with a drop of port, that's all, I don't drink really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 You signed this as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Oh yes, I think I signed it two or three times. Well of course we never had drink in the home you see, we were really a family like -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Were you strictly teetotal or would your mother have a glass of port if she felt ill or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Well no she wouldn't have port, I think that she has had brandy, which is really cal
led for a medicine really. Yes. Only occasionally, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did the temperance club have any special outings or activities?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Don't remember the temperance side of it, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Were there any other clubs or social activities organised by the chapel you went to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Yes, they had a - Girls Brigade.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 On the lines of the Boys Brigade?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Yes. Then, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 What sort of things did you do in that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Well }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5572215\charrsid7944611 exercises}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611  and things like that, but I don't remember very much - it didn't - form really - too long, you know, it was just one of those things they couldn't get the children in to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Was grace said at meals in your family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Well I should imagine it - it would have been. With my father. Mother being - like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Were you taught to say prayers at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 
Yes. And father used to - read - a Bible - a passage of scripture out the Bible, say two or three passages - from the Bible, from a chapter. And if we wanted to stay up late we used to ask him - we not got it - you know, we 
took it all in but - we could stay up a bit late if he read a bit more. Used to have a lamp on the table in those days you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 This was every night was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Every night, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did you ever have family prayers, all of you together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did your father take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Oh rather, yes. Down Islington Green - Clerkenwell Green and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Do you know what his views were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 He was - Liberal. And - Lloyd George's - lot you know. He used - he used to say that - he used to talk to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3679910\charrsid7944611 George}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611  Lansbury, he used to - go round - those meetings in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Was your father actually a member of the party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did he do any work at election time for them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No. Only putting a - a big bill in the window.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did he take part in any other political activity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Do you remember why he held those views, did he talk about them in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Oh - I don't know about reasons why but he used to - read a lot and we - off like you know - that kind o
f thing and - we used - we used to get to know about things through him. Otherwise I mean we didn't know anything outside.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Was your mother interested in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No. No, never heard her speak about -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Do you know if she voted before 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No. No. No, mother died 1914.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Do you remember your father voting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Oh yes, he would vote - definitely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 In some places at that time men felt they risked losing their job or their house if they voted differently from their employers, do y
ou know if your father ever felt himself under this sort of pressure at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 I don't think so. Don't remember that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 You told me that at the place you worked they advised you against having anything to do with the unions?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Not to - not to jo
in the union, if the - union men were outside, which they know they were going to be outside, we were not to - have anything to do with them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Do you remember anyone getting into trouble at work or getting the sack for their union activities?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No. No. No, didn't bother about it at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 When your parents were not at work how did they spend their time, what sort of leisure activities did your parents have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Well I think father used to do little jobs about the house. And he would - of course
 he would be - he would go out every day, I mean, to see whether he could get - any little jobs, any off jobs, 'cos he was only a painter and decorator.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did your mother have any interests outside the home? Did she go out at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 The only thing mother used to do was go out shopping.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 That's the only time she'd go out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 That's - I think so. She used to be out in the garden most of the time you know, she used to like her little garden.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 How many evenings a week would your father spend at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Every evening. Never went -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did he have a regular time for getting in from work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No, I don't think they used to in those days because they used to work here 'til eight o'clock at night some of the men. Any time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did your father take part in any sports?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did he ever go to the races or bet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 
Oh no. Oh no. In fact he wouldn't have the money, I think they were against that kind of thing you now. A little place we used to go to off Potters Bar. Down one of the co
untry lanes, and it was a - little village Post Office, but they had a lovely garden, and they always knew we were coming there, because it was the usual once a month Saturday afternoon, and tea were already laid out for us. And we used to go and have to 
have a wash and brush up you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 This would be ordered before hand would it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 
Yes. And they used to allow us to go into their rooms upstairs. To have a wash and brush up. Then we sit down to tea and have our tea and then afterwards there was a piano in the room and we could get up and - dance round and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Almost like a club house in a way for you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Yes, it was, yes. South Mimms. That's where it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 This was your cycling club days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did you take up any other sporting activities at this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No, it was mostly cycling.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Were there plenty of tea shops round in those days?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Not there where we went, it was just a little village.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 If you were cycling in a strange area where you hadn't been before would there be a tea shop in every village?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Oh definitely, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 After you started work how did you spend your evenings, winter evenings when you wouldn't be out cycling or things like this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Well we probably - be sitting at the table pla
ying little - table games. Or I'd be - doing a little bit of - sewing, I used to love sewing in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Even after doing it all day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Yes, oh yes. Yes. There was another place we used to go to. Once in - perhaps a couple of months. That was -
 Ickleford, near Hitchin. Hertfordshire. And we used to be there for weekends. Yes. Lovely times there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Was this another tea shop type place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 No, it was two elderly ladies - sisters, and they used to - have - people come weekends to stay just fo
r over the weekend. And - it was really lovely there. That was when - one of the - club - club - boys said, would I like to go - on - our Captain's - the two bicycles, you know, the - tandem together, he would take me into Bedford. And - oh yes, so I said
,
 oh yes, I'd like to come. So we both got on the bicycle, this thing and - everything was going all right 'til we got to a hill. And as we were going down this hill, I didn't - we didn't know, he should have known, it was a fixed wheel. And of course as w
e
 was going round and round and round, well we both of us put our legs out like that and down the bottom there was a sharp turn. Oh I was frightened. And anyway he said, keep your head, we'll be all right. But of course round the bottom there was a farmer 
coming with a load of cows. And didn't he }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5572215\charrsid7944611 swear as}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 
 we went by, but it's a wonder we weren't - smashed to pieces. But - we did - 'cos as we turned the corner and it went up - kind of an incline again we lost our }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5572215\charrsid7944611 speed}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 . But oh it was terrible. I'll never forget it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Was cycling quite a common activity by this time, were there lots of cycling clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Wouldn't say there was a terrible lot but there were a lot, there were a lot on the roads. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 After you started work did you make now friends at this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Other then your childhood friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Where did you meet them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 
Well there were two - two women came from - Plaistow, near Canning Town and - they invited me over to their - home. And they - wanted me - they - their idea was to take me to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 These were the two that took you to the music hall?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 The music hall.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 You must these two at work did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did you ever bring your friends home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Very very occasionally because we hadn't - got the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5572215\charrsid7944611 wherewithal}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611  to - to - this was after you mean, after I left - after I left school, yes. Mother didn't mind but - we - no, not very much. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 You'd be about twenty-one or two in 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did you have any special friends at this time, boys or girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Oh never had any special boyfriends. Just the club and the girls, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did your parents meet your friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Not very often because they never came to the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did your parents expect to know where you were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Did you have to be in by a certain time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 
Mother used to like us to be in. There was one occasion, I can always remember my mother saying - one of the - friends that I had there, she lived at Wood Green, and she asked me over to her home, and I came home a bit late on a Saturday evening.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 What would be a bit late?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 
Well I would say about nine o'clock in those days, 'cos it was winter and it was dark. But on this occasion it wasn't - it was - must have been sum
mer because I can remember mother being in the garden - waiting for me to come along, and she was talking to a neighbour. And I heard her say, well you know I like to know where they - go to and when it gets late you get a bit worried being girls you know
. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 You did have a reasonable amount of freedom if you used to go away for the weekends with the cycling club and this sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Oh well then mother had died then you see, well it was 1914 mother died and that was after 1914, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 So your father wasn't -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Oh father didn't mind. You know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 He'd trust you to look after yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 
Oh yes. Yes. These friends of mine - that lived at Plaistow, I don't know whether - you heard about it, there was a big - explosion at Silver 
Town. And I was - we were working, we just left work at half past six, I worked in Goswell Road, and - oh - the flames - we saw it in the sky, this terrible red colour. And it was tremendous, it was right across the sky, that was - that was Goswell Road. 
A
nd this was Silver Town. And - this friend of mine, she said - oh anyway, she - we went - she went home and I went my home. Well next morning we went in to work, her father worked - at this place. It was what they used to call the soda works, I - I think 
it was something to do with - ammunition. And - she said - well it was a terrible affair really, I think - oh hundreds were killed and burnt and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Do you remember what year this was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 It was during - it - must have been the first - must have b
een the first year of the war, yes it was, 1914 upwards war because - we thought it was something to do with the enemy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 So it would be 1914 or '15?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 It would be, yes. Yes. And anyway, her father hadn't been well, and he didn't go in so therefore 
he was one that - but she took me - so after that, about - say a month after - she said would I like to go over and see it. And of course we didn't know what damage was then, I mean, 'course we know now what damage can be done with bombs. I'd never seen a
n
ything like it. And there was a church standing with - it was like a shell. And yet - a couple were getting married. And we just happened to see that going on you know. But I've never seen anything like it - not then, I mean we would now, we wouldn't take
 all that much notice but - this huge building was all twisted and - all the ironwork twisted, it was a - must have been a terrible thing at the time.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7213291 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 We get rather used to this sort of thing now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6950340 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072855\charrsid7944611 Yes, we get - we have since, yes. But then it - 
of course it was - something you thought you'd never forget you know. Yes, that was one of the things that happened.
\par }}